description: Impress your lunch guests with this slow-cooked zucchini and feta frittata recipe, which also boasts tomato, spinach, red onion and parmesan.
name: Slow Cooker Zucchini & Feta Frittata Recipe | Woolworths
recipeIngredient: 1 red onion, cut into thin wedges

HowToTip.tipText: If your slow cooker doesn’t have a ‘sear’ mode for step 1, use a medium frying pan over medium heat.

recipeInstructions.text: Heat oil in 5.5L slow cooker in sear mode. Cook zucchini and onion, uncovered, for 2 minutes or until golden and slightly softened. Transfer mixture to a bowl.
Meanwhile, whisk eggs, milk and parmesan together in a large jug. Season.

HowToTip.tipText: To line the slow cooker with baking paper, scrunch up the paper, then flatten it out before placing it in slow-cooker bowl.

recipeInstructions.text: Wipe out slow cooker, then grease and line with baking paper (see Tip). Add zucchini mixture, tomato, feta and half of the spinach. Pour egg mixture over veggies, cover with lid and cook on low for 4 hours or until eggs are set. Remove frittata from slow cooker and allow to cool for 15 minutes. Slice and serve with remaining spinach.
